02/07/2006
ZAGREB, Croatia -- ODIHR chief Christian Strohal on Friday (30 June) praised efforts by Croatia's authorities to combat hate-motivated crime in the country. 
He was speaking at a pilot programme -- co-organised by the OSCE, the United Kingdom and the United States -- to train police investigating and responding to such crimes.
In other news Friday, an Adriatic Euro region including Albania, Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, Italy, Montenegro and Slovenia officially opened in the Croatian town of Pula, where the initiative will be based. 
The project is aimed at strengthening institutional collaboration and enhancing economic development in the Adriatic region. 
(Vecernji list, Vjesnik - 01/07/06; OSCE Web site, HINA - 30/06/06)
